http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/andhra-pradesh/HC-directive-on-chemical-ripening-of-fruits/article14015595.ece

A Division Bench of the High Court at Hyderabad comprising of Acting Chief Justice D.B. Bhosale and Justice S.V. Bhatt on Friday directed the Principal Secretaries of Agricultural and Marketing Department of Andhra Pradesh and Telangana to appear in person on February 1.The Bench was ordering their presence in a taken up PIL regarding the usage of harmful chemicals for ripening fruits. The Bench heard the arguments on behalf of the two State Governments. The Bench expressed its dismay at the manner in which local press reports are filed before the court. At one stage, the Bench commented that there are no genuine efforts but reports are generated.The Bench asked the officers from both States to appear in person in this issue so that some concrete steps may be put in place.AP, TS officials told to appear in court on February 1